    <string-array name="tour_descriptions">
        <item>The Uluwatu Temple is a stunning sea temple perched on a cliff with a breathtaking view of the Indian Ocean.</item>
        <item>Visit the Sacred Monkey Forest in Ubud, home to hundreds of playful long-tailed macaques.</item>
        <item>Tanah Lot is one of Bali iconic sea temples, known for its incredible sunset views.</item>
        <item>Climb Mount Batur for a spectacular sunrise view from an active volcano.</item>
        <item>Explore Nusa Penida’s stunning beaches, cliffs, and crystal-clear waters.</item>
        <item>Jatiluwih offers magnificent terraced rice fields with breathtaking mountain views.</item>
        <item>Besakih Temple is Bali’s Mother Temple, located on the majestic Mount Agung.</item>
        <item>Tirta Empul is a sacred water temple where visitors can participate in a purification ritual.</item>
        <item>Sekumpul Waterfall is one of the most beautiful waterfalls in Bali, surrounded by lush green nature.</item>
        <item>Manta Point is a famous dive spot in Nusa Penida, where you can swim with manta rays.</item>
